    {
        "content": "<p><code>\\o</code> is shorter, and it's <code>function.comp</code></p>",
        "id": 219407245,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1607552257
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But if you're like me, with years of latex-induced muscle memory, <code>\\circ</code> works too :)</p>",
        "id": 219407484,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1607552342
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>One of the neatest things about the shortcuts is that most of the maths symbols are either the same as LaTeX, or the same as the LaTeX shortcut I usually use to define them (e.g. <code>\\Q</code>).</p>",
        "id": 219413162,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1607555385
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Sure, but who actually uses \\McC?</p>",
        "id": 219413247,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1607555427
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I use \\Ccal</p>",
        "id": 219413260,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1607555439
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah that's the exception. I always say to myself \"MATHcal\"</p>",
        "id": 219413421,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1607555556
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>OOOH! Now I'll actually remember it!</p>",
        "id": 219413438,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1607555570
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Of course you can just add <code>\\Xcal</code> to the list of shortcuts, there's just a file on github somewhere</p>",
        "id": 219413480,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1607555596
    },
